# OpenShift AI Installation Toolkit

Automation toolkit for OpenShift + Red Hat OpenShift AI (RHOAI) on AWS with GPU support, MaaS, and GenAI.

## Entry Points

| Script | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `rhoai-toolkit.sh` | Main interactive menu (start here) |
| `scripts/install-rhoai-34.sh` | RHOAI 3.4 direct install (recommended) |
| `scripts/install-rhoai-33.sh` | RHOAI 3.3 direct install |
| `Makefile` | CLI automation targets |

## Directory Layout

- `scripts/` — Standalone utility scripts (install, deploy, cleanup)
- `lib/functions/` — Reusable bash functions (rhoai.sh, operators.sh, model-deployment.sh)
- `lib/manifests/` — Kubernetes YAML templates (operators, rhoai, rhcl, templates)
- `lib/utils/` — Utility libraries (os-compat.sh, colors.sh, common.sh, rhoai-version.sh)
- `demo/` — Demo apps (maas-demo, llamastack-demo, guardrails-demo)
- `docs/guides/` — How-to guides; `docs/reference/` — Technical reference
- `docs/TROUBLESHOOTING.md` — All troubleshooting in one place

## Critical Gotchas

### Hardware Profiles (RHOAI 3.x)
MUST include scheduling section with tolerations for GPU:
```yaml
spec:
  scheduling:
    type: Node
    node:
      nodeSelector:
        nvidia.com/gpu.present: 'true'
      tolerations:
        - key: nvidia.com/gpu
          operator: Exists
          effect: NoSchedule
```
Deployed models MUST have ALL THREE annotations for dashboard to show correct profile name:
- `opendatahub.io/hardware-profile-name`
- `opendatahub.io/hardware-profile-namespace`
- `opendatahub.io/hardware-profile-resource-version` (fetched from HardwareProfile metadata at deploy time)

### Model Serving CRs — Depends on Runtime, NOT RHOAI Version
- **llm-d** → `LLMInferenceService` (serving.kserve.io/v1alpha1) — primary runtime for MaaS
- **vLLM on MaaS** → `InferenceService` + MaaS (RHOAI 3.4 TP: enable `vLLMDeploymentOnMaaS` dashboard flag)
- **Everything else** (vLLM, vLLM-Omni, OpenVINO, Caikit-TGIS, NIM, MLServer) → `InferenceService` (serving.kserve.io/v1beta1)

### MaaS
- **RHOAI 3.4**: MaaS core GA. Subscription-based CRDs replace tier ConfigMaps.
  - TLS: OpenShift service-ca (NOT cert-manager Certificate)
  - Gateway needs: `opendatahub.io/managed: "false"` + `security.opendatahub.io/authorino-tls-bootstrap: "true"`
  - Dashboard flags: `modelAsService`, `maasAuthPolicies`, `genAiStudio` (required); `observabilityDashboard`, `vLLMDeploymentOnMaaS` (optional TP)
  - CRDs: MaaSSubscription, MaaSAuthPolicy, MaaSModelRef, Tenant, ExternalModel
  - RHCL v1.2+ required. Tenant auto-created in `models-as-a-service` namespace.
  - Sub-features still TP: vLLM runtime, external OIDC, observability dashboard, external model egress.
- **RHOAI 3.3**: MaaS Tech Preview. Tier-based ConfigMaps. cert-manager for TLS. Only llm-d runtime.
- **RHOAI 3.3+**: integrated via `modelsAsService` in DSC, endpoint `inference-gateway.apps.<cluster>`
- **RHOAI 3.2-**: legacy kustomize setup, endpoint `maas.<cluster>/maas-api/v1/...`

### Feature Store (Feast) Dashboard Visibility
Requires: label `feature-store-ui: enabled`, `spec.services.registry.local.server.restAPI: true`, namespace labeled `opendatahub.io/dashboard=true`

### Trainer (Kubeflow v2)
Requires JobSet operator installed first. Use `trainer` not `trainingoperator` in DSC.

### Tool Calling (vLLM)
Parsers: `hermes` (Qwen), `llama3_json` (Llama), `mistral` (Mistral)

## Code Style

- Use `lib/utils/os-compat.sh` for macOS/Linux compat (grep_perl, base64_encode, sed_inplace, etc.)
- Colors from `lib/utils/colors.sh`
- Functions sourced from `lib/functions/`
- Templates use `envsubst` for variable substitution
- All scripts must work on both macOS and Linux
